page.title: 01Templecome, in Somerset
page.content: Undulating area, western edge of Blackmore vale. Scarp in West falls to the west. Low ridge runs NNW-SSE sloping to east and cut by several small strea s. High point at Wilkinthrop in the North-West 505 feet. Major settlement, Templecombe, in the North-east lies on the London-Exeter railway and Wincanton-Blandford road (A357). Small agricultural communication at Yenston, Bowden and Stowell are separaged by small farms. Railway runs East-West across Northern part of area. Main road North-South in the East. Minor roads, East-West follow high ground. Infrequent bus service to Wincanton/Yeovil. Trains 2 hourly Maire employes Plessey (Electronics) at Templecombe and wilkingthrop House. Numbers of people commute to Yeovil and Wincanton. Otherwise agriculture.
